article.description: — Jubrile Belo registered 14 points and seven rebounds as Montana State topped Northern Arizona 62-51 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Belo scores 14 to lead Montana St. over N. Arizona 62-51
article.linkText: Belo scores 14 to lead Montana St. over N. Arizona 62-51
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- — Jubrile Belo registered 14 points and seven rebounds as Montana State topped Northern Arizona 62-51 on Thursday night. Xavier Bishop had 12 points for Montana State (8-3, 5-0 Big Sky Conference) and Amin Adamu added nine points and eight rebounds. The Bobcats have won six in a row for the first time since the 2003-04 season and had five straight wins to open the Big Sky season for the for the first time since 2004-05. Cameron Shelton had 24 points and six rebounds for the Lumberjacks (4-10, 3-5). The Bobcats and Lumberjacks square off again in Flagstaff on Saturday ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
